msgstr "10. The training rule on kings"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.220"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-np.10.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.62"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2070"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa upaṭṭhāko "
"mahāmatto āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa dūtena cīvaracetāpannaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr ""
"At that time a minister who was a supporter of Venerable Upananda sent a "
"robe fund to Upananda by messenger, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid ""
"“iminā cīvaracetāpannena cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena "
"acchādehī”ti."
msgstr "“Buy a robe with this fund and give it to Venerable Upananda.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "Atha kho so dūto yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The messenger went to Upananda"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "“idaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmantaṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable, I’ve brought a robe fund for you."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhātu āyasmā cīvaracetāpannan”ti."
msgstr "Please accept it.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ dūtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid ""
"“na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, cīvaracetāpannaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma, cīvarañca kho mayaṃ "
"paṭiggaṇhāma kālena kappiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“We don’t receive robe funds, but we do receive allowable robes at the right "
"time.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, so dūto āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "“atthi panāyasmato koci veyyāvaccakaro”ti?"
msgstr "“Is there anyone who provides services for you?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako ārāmaṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr "Just then a lay follower had come to the monastery on some business."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ dūtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Upananda told the messenger,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "“eso kho, āvuso, upāsako bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccakaro”ti."
msgstr "“This lay follower provides services for the monks.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.63"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so dūto taṃ upāsakaṃ saññāpetvā yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"The messenger instructed that lay follower and then returned to Upananda"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid "“yaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmā veyyāvaccakaraṃ niddisi saññatto so mayā."
msgstr "“I’ve instructed the lay follower you pointed out to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.18"
msgid "Upasaṅkamatu āyasmā kālena, cīvarena taṃ acchādessatī”ti."
msgstr "Please approach him at the right time and he’ll give you a robe.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2071"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.19"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena so mahāmatto āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa "
"santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "Later on that minister sent a message to Upananda, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.20"
msgid "“paribhuñjatu ayyo taṃ cīvaraṃ,"
msgstr "“Please use the robe;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.21"
msgid "icchāma mayaṃ ayyena taṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuttan”ti."
msgstr "we wish you to use the robe.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.22"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ upāsakaṃ na kiñci avacāsi."
msgstr "But Upananda did not say anything to that lay follower."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.23"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho so mahāmatto āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa santike dūtaṃ "
"pāhesi—"
msgstr "The minister sent the same message a second time,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.24"
msgid ""
"“paribhuñjatu ayyo taṃ cīvaraṃ, icchāma mayaṃ ayyena taṃ cīvaraṃ "
"paribhuttan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.25"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ upāsakaṃ na kiñci avacāsi."
msgstr "but again Upananda did nothing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.26"
msgid ""
"Tatiyampi kho so mahāmatto āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa santike dūtaṃ "
"pāhesi—"
msgstr "The minister then sent the message a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.1.27"
msgid ""
"“paribhuñjatu ayyo taṃ cīvaraṃ, icchāma mayaṃ ayyena taṃ cīvaraṃ "
"paribhuttan”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.1.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2072"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena negamassa samayo hoti."
msgstr "On that occasion the townspeople were having a community meeting,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "Negamena ca katikā katā hoti—"
msgstr "and an agreement had been made"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "“yo pacchā āgacchati paññāsaṃ baddho”ti."
msgstr "that whoever came late would be fined fifty coins."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.64"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto yena so upāsako tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Just then Upananda went to that lay follower"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ upāsakaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "“attho me, āvuso, cīvarenā”ti."
msgstr "“I need a robe.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "“Ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehi, ajja negamassa samayo."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, please wait one day, for today there is a community meeting,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid "Negamena ca katikā katā hoti—‘yo pacchā āgacchati paññāsaṃ baddho’”ti."
msgstr ""
"and an agreement has been made that whoever comes late gets fined fifty "
"coins."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid "“Ajjeva me, āvuso, cīvaraṃ dehī”ti"
msgstr "“Give me the robe today,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "ovaṭṭikāya parāmasi."
msgstr "and he grabbed him by the belt."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so upāsako āyasmatā upanandena sakyaputtena nippīḷiyamāno āyasmato "
"upanandassa sakyaputtassa cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā pacchā agamāsi."
msgstr ""
"Being pressured by Upananda, the lay follower bought him a robe, and as a "
"consequence he was late for the meeting."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid "Manussā taṃ upāsakaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "People asked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "“kissa tvaṃ, ayyo, pacchā āgato,"
msgstr "“Sir, why are you late?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "paññāsaṃ jīnosī”ti."
msgstr "You’ve just lost fifty coins.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.221"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2073"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid "Atha kho so upāsako tesaṃ manussānaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "That lay follower told them what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "And they grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid "“mahicchā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā asantuṭṭhā."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics have great desires; they are not content."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid "Nayimesaṃ sukaraṃ veyyāvaccampi kātuṃ."
msgstr "Even to provide them with a service isn’t easy."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando upāsakena—"
msgstr "How can Venerable Upananda not agree when he’s asked by a lay follower"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid "‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehī’ti vuccamāno nāgamessatī”ti."
msgstr "to wait for a day?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2074"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.21"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.22"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.23"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.24"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto upāsakena—"
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda not agree when asked by a lay follower"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.25"
msgid "‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehī’ti vuccamāno nāgamessatī”ti."
msgstr "to wait for a day?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2075"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.26"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena "
"vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.65"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.27"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, upāsakena—"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.28"
msgid "‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehī’ti vuccamāno nāgamesī”ti?"
msgstr "that you acted like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.29"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.30"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.31"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, upāsakena—"
msgstr "“… Foolish man, how can you not agree when asked by a lay follower"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.32"
msgid "‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamehī’ti vuccamāno nāgamessasi."
msgstr "to wait for a day?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.33"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.2.34"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.222"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.1.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2076"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissa rājā vā rājabhoggo vā brāhmaṇo vā gahapatiko vā "
"dūtena cīvaracetāpannaṃ pahiṇeyya—"
msgstr ""
"‘If a king, a king’s employee, a brahmin, or a householder sends a robe fund "
"for a monk by messenger, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.2"
msgid ""
"‘iminā cīvaracetāpannena cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ cīvarena "
"acchādehī’ti."
msgstr "‘Buy a robe with this robe fund and give it to monk so-and-so,’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.3"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "and the messenger goes to that monk and says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.4"
msgid "‘idaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmantaṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ,"
msgstr "‘Venerable, I have brought a robe fund for you;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.5"
msgid "paṭiggaṇhātu āyasmā cīvaracetāpannan’ti,"
msgstr "please accept it,’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.6"
msgid "tena bhikkhunā so dūto evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "then that monk should reply,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.7"
msgid "‘na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, cīvaracetāpannaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr "‘We don’t receive robe funds,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.8"
msgid "Cīvarañca kho mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma, kālena kappiyan’ti."
msgstr "but we do receive allowable robes at the right time.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.9"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "If that messenger says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.10"
msgid "‘atthi panāyasmato koci veyyāvaccakaro’ti,"
msgstr "‘Is there anyone who provides services for you?’,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.11"
msgid ""
"cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro niddisitabbo ārāmiko vā "
"upāsako vā—"
msgstr ""
"the monk, if he needs a robe, should point out a monastery attendant or a "
"lay follower and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.12"
msgid "‘eso kho, āvuso, bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccakaro’ti."
msgstr "‘He provides services for the monks.’"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.66"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.13"
msgid ""
"So ce dūto taṃ veyyāvaccakaraṃ saññāpetvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ "
"vadeyya—"
msgstr ""
"If the messenger instructs that service-provider and then returns to the "
"monk and says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.14"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmā veyyāvaccakaraṃ niddisi saññatto so mayā,"
msgstr "‘Venerable, I have instructed the service-provider you pointed out;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.15"
msgid "upasaṅkamatu āyasmā kālena, cīvarena taṃ acchādessatī’ti,"
msgstr "please approach him at the right time and he will give you a robe,’"

#. VAR: dvattikkhattuṃ → dvittikkhattuṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.16"
msgid ""
"cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro upasaṅkamitvā "
"dvattikkhattuṃ codetabbo sāretabbo—"
msgstr ""
"then, if that monk needs a robe, he should approach that service-provider "
"and prompt him and remind him two or three times, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.17"
msgid "‘attho me, āvuso, cīvarenā’ti."
msgstr "‘I need a robe.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.18"
msgid ""
"Dvattikkhattuṃ codayamāno sārayamāno taṃ cīvaraṃ abhinipphādeyya, iccetaṃ "
"kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he then gets a robe, that is good."

#. VAR: chakkhattuparamaṃ → chakkhattuṃ paramaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.19"
msgid ""
"no ce abhinipphādeyya, catukkhattuṃ pañcakkhattuṃ chakkhattuparamaṃ "
"tuṇhībhūtena uddissa ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he does not get it, he should stand in silence for it at most six times."

#. VAR: kusalaṃ; tato → kusalaṃ no ce abhi­nip­phā­deyya tato (syā2, syā3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.20"
msgid ""
"Catukkhattuṃ pañcakkhattuṃ chakkhattuparamaṃ tuṇhībhūto uddissa tiṭṭhamāno "
"taṃ cīvaraṃ abhinipphādeyya, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he then gets a robe, that is good."

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.21"
msgid ""
"tato ce uttari vāyamamāno taṃ cīvaraṃ abhinipphādeyya, nissaggiyaṃ "
"pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he makes any further effort and then gets a robe, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.22"
msgid ""
"No ce abhinipphādeyya, yatassa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ, tattha sāmaṃ vā "
"gantabbaṃ dūto vā pāhetabbo—"
msgstr ""
"If he does not get a robe, he should go to the owner of that robe fund, or "
"send a message:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.23"
msgid ""
"‘yaṃ kho tumhe āyasmanto bhikkhuṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ pahiṇittha, na "
"taṃ tassa bhikkhuno kiñci atthaṃ anubhoti,"
msgstr ""
"‘Sirs, that monk hasn’t received any benefit from the robe fund you sent for "
"him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.24"
msgid "yuñjantāyasmanto sakaṃ,"
msgstr "Please take action over what’s yours;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.25"
msgid "mā vo sakaṃ vinassā’ti,"
msgstr "let it not be lost.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.26"
msgid "ayaṃ tattha sāmīcī”ti."
msgstr "This is the proper procedure.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs1.3.27"
msgid "(<em>10</em>:<strong>29</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-np.10.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2077"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissāti"
msgstr "For a monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "bhikkhussatthāya, bhikkhuṃ ārammaṇaṃ karitvā, bhikkhuṃ acchādetukāmo."
msgstr ""
"for the benefit of a monk; making a monk the object of consideration, one "
"desires to give to him."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2078"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "Rājā nāma"
msgstr "A king:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "yo koci rajjaṃ kāreti."
msgstr "whoever rules."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.67"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2079"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Rājabhoggo nāma"
msgstr "A king’s employee:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "yo koci rañño bhattavetanāhāro."
msgstr "whoever gets food and wages from a king."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2080"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Brāhmaṇo nāma"
msgstr "A brahmin:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "jātiyā brāhmaṇo."
msgstr "a brahmin by birth."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2081"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "Gahapatiko nāma"
msgstr "A householder:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "ṭhapetvā rājaṃ rājabhoggaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ avaseso gahapatiko nāma."
msgstr "anyone apart from a king, a king’s employee, and a brahmin."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2082"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Cīvaracetāpannaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A robe fund:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "hiraññaṃ vā suvaṇṇaṃ vā muttā vā maṇi vā."
msgstr "money, gold, a pearl, or a gem."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2083"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "Iminā cīvaracetāpannenāti"
msgstr "With this robe fund:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "paccupaṭṭhitena."
msgstr "with that which is at one’s disposal."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2084"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Cetāpetvāti"
msgstr "Buy:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "parivattetvā."
msgstr "having exchanged."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2085"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "Acchādehīti"
msgstr "Give:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "dajjehi."
msgstr "donate."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2086"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "And the messenger goes to that monk and says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "“idaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmantaṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable, I have brought a robe fund for you;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "Paṭiggaṇhātu āyasmā cīvaracetāpannan”ti,"
msgstr "please accept it,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "tena bhikkhunā so dūto evamassa vacanīyo—"
msgstr "then that monk should reply,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid "“na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, cīvaracetāpannaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr "“We don’t receive robe funds,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.24"
msgid "Cīvarañca kho mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma, kālena kappiyan”ti."
msgstr "but we do receive allowable robes at the right time.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.25"
msgid "So ce dūto taṃ bhikkhuṃ evaṃ vadeyya—"
msgstr "If that messenger says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.26"
msgid "“atthi panāyasmato koci veyyāvaccakaro”ti?"
msgstr "“Is there anyone who provides services for you?”,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.27"
msgid ""
"Cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro niddisitabbo ārāmiko vā "
"upāsako vā—"
msgstr ""
"the monk, if he needs a robe, should point out a monastery attendant or a "
"lay follower and say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.28"
msgid "“eso kho, āvuso, bhikkhūnaṃ veyyāvaccakaro”ti."
msgstr "“He provides services for the monks”:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.29"
msgid "Na vattabbo—"
msgstr "he should not say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.30"
msgid ""
"“tassa dehīti vā, so vā nikkhipissati, so vā parivattessati, so vā "
"cetāpessatī”ti."
msgstr "“Give it to him/he’ll put it aside/he’ll do the exchange/he’ll buy it.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2087"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.31"
msgid ""
"So ce dūto taṃ veyyāvaccakaraṃ saññāpetvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ "
"vadeyya—"
msgstr ""
"If the messenger instructs that service-provider and then returns to the "
"monk and says,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.32"
msgid "“yaṃ kho, bhante, āyasmā veyyāvaccakaraṃ niddisi saññatto so mayā."
msgstr "“Venerable, I have instructed the service-provider you pointed out;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.33"
msgid "Upasaṅkamatu āyasmā kālena, cīvarena taṃ acchādessatī”ti."
msgstr "please approach him at the right time and he will give you a robe,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.34"
msgid ""
"Cīvaratthikena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā veyyāvaccakaro upasaṅkamitvā "
"dvattikkhattuṃ codetabbo sāretabbo—"
msgstr ""
"then, if that monk needs a robe, he should approach that service-provider "
"and prompt him and remind him two or three times, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.35"
msgid "“attho me, āvuso, cīvarenā”ti."
msgstr "“I need a robe”:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.36"
msgid "Na vattabbo—"
msgstr "he should not say,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.37"
msgid ""
"“dehi me cīvaraṃ, āhara me cīvaraṃ, parivattehi me cīvaraṃ, cetāpehi me "
"cīvaran”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Give me a robe/get me a robe/get a robe in exchange for me/buy me a robe.”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.223"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2088"></a><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.38"
msgid "Dutiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "He should say it a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.39"
msgid "Tatiyampi vattabbo."
msgstr "and a third time."

#. </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.40"
msgid "Sace abhinipphādeti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;"
msgstr "If he gets it, that is good."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.41"
msgid "no ce abhinipphādeti, tattha gantvā tuṇhībhūtena uddissa ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he does not get it, [he should go there and] he should stand in silence "
"for it:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.42"
msgid "Na āsane nisīditabbaṃ."
msgstr "he should not sit down on a seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.43"
msgid "Na āmisaṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should not accept a gift."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.68"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.44"
msgid "Na dhammo bhāsitabbo."
msgstr "He should not give a teaching."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.45"
msgid "“Kiṃ kāraṇā āgatosī”ti pucchiyamāno"
msgstr "If he is asked, “Why have you come?”,"

#. <i lang="pli">Jānāhi</i>. This verb, which normally means “to understand” or “to find out,” is used quite broadly in the Pali canon.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.46"
msgid "“jānāhi, āvuso”ti vattabbo."
msgstr "he should say, “Think about it.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.47"
msgid ""
"Sace āsane vā nisīdati, āmisaṃ vā paṭiggaṇhāti, dhammaṃ vā bhāsati, ṭhānaṃ "
"bhañjati."
msgstr ""
"If he sits down on a seat, or he accepts a gift, or he gives a teaching, he "
"loses one allowance to stand."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2089"></a><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.48"
msgid "Dutiyampi ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "He should stand a second"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.49"
msgid "Tatiyampi ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "and a third time."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.50"
msgid "Catukkhattuṃ codetvā catukkhattuṃ ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts four times, he can stand four times."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.51"
msgid "Pañcakkhattuṃ codetvā dvikkhattuṃ ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts five times, he can stand twice."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.1.52"
msgid "Chakkhattuṃ codetvā na ṭhātabbaṃ."
msgstr "If he prompts six times, he cannot stand at all."

#. </span></p><hr><p><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.2.2"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vāyamamāno taṃ cīvaraṃ abhinipphādeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he makes any further effort and the robe then appears, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct for the effort."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.69"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ "
"ṭhānena abhinipphāditaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this robe which I got after prompting more than three times and "
"standing more than six times is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2090"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.11"
msgid ""
"No ce abhinipphādeyya, yatassa cīvaracetāpannaṃ ābhataṃ tattha sāmaṃ vā "
"gantabbaṃ dūto vā pāhetabbo—"
msgstr ""
"If he does not get a robe, he should go to the owner of that robe fund, or "
"send a message:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.12"
msgid ""
"“yaṃ kho tumhe, āyasmanto, bhikkhuṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ pahiṇittha na "
"taṃ tassa bhikkhuno kiñci atthaṃ anubhoti."
msgstr ""
"‘Sirs, that monk hasn’t received any benefit from the robe fund you sent for "
"him."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.13"
msgid "Yuñjantāyasmanto sakaṃ,"
msgstr "Please take action over what’s yours;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.14"
msgid "mā vo sakaṃ vinassā”ti."
msgstr "let it not be lost.’"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2091"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.15"
msgid "Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti"
msgstr "This is the proper procedure:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.2.16"
msgid "ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā."
msgstr "this is the right method."

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2092"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid ""
"Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena atirekasaññī "
"abhinipphādeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he prompts more than three times and stands more than six times, and he "
"perceives that he has done so, and he gets a robe, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid ""
"Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena vematiko "
"abhinipphādeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he prompts more than three times and stands more than six times, but he "
"is unsure if he has, and he gets a robe, he commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid ""
"Atirekatikkhattuṃ codanāya atirekachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena ūnakasaññī "
"abhinipphādeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If he prompts more than three times and stands more than six times, but he "
"perceives that it is less, and he gets a robe, he commits an offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2093"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid ""
"Ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena atirekasaññī, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times, but he "
"perceives that it is more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid ""
"Ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena vematiko, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times, but he "
"is unsure if he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "Ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena ūnakasaññī anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times, and he "
"perceives that it is less, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.10.2.4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2094"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.2"
msgid "tikkhattuṃ codanāya, chakkhattuṃ ṭhānena,"
msgstr "if he prompts three times and stands six time;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.70"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.3"
msgid "ūnakatikkhattuṃ codanāya, ūnakachakkhattuṃ ṭhānena,"
msgstr "if he prompts less than three times and stands less than six times;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.4"
msgid "acodiyamāno deti,"
msgstr "if it is given without prompting;"

#. I am unable to make sense of the phrasing in the non-offense clause (<i lang="pli">sāmikā codetvā denti</i>), and I therefore translate according to the phrasing in the commentary, “After prompting by the owners, it is given;” <i lang="pli">sāmikehi codetvā dinne</i>, see <ref>Kkh. 119.6</ref>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.5"
msgid "sāmikā codetvā denti,"
msgstr "if the owners prompt and then it is given;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.6"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.7"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2095"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.8"
msgid "Rājasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr "The tenth rule, the training rule on kings, is finished."

#. </p><p class="endchapter"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.9"
msgid "Kathinavaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr "The first chapter on the robe-making season is finished."

#. </p><p class="endsection summary"><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2096"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.10"
msgid "Tassuddānaṃ"
msgstr "This is the summary:"

#. </p><p class="uddana"><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2097"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.11"
msgid "Ubbhataṃ kathinaṃ tīṇi,"
msgstr "Three on the ended robe-making season,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.12"
msgid "dhovanañca paṭiggaho;"
msgstr "And washing, receiving;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.13"
msgid "Aññātakāni tīṇeva,"
msgstr "Three on those who are unrelated,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np10:pts-cs2.4.14"
msgid "ubhinnaṃ dūtakena cāti."
msgstr "Of both, and with messenger."

